ls - list the files and directories

1. open the last edited file using ls -t

ls -t | head -1

2. display one file per line & detailed information about the files
  ls -l

3.display in human redable formata
  ls -lh

4.for directory information
  ls -ld /etc
here -l means long listing files
    -d means directories

5. order file based on last modified time using 
  ls -lt

6. ls -ltr  means in 
  -l = shows detailed info like size, permission and modification time
  -t = sort file by last modified time 
  -r = reversed the order (oldest first)

7. for hidden files 
ls -a

8 . display the inode number
ls -i

9.to disply auser id and group id 
ls -n ~/kv

8.ls -A   (show hidde files but one the '.' current directory & '..' parent directory)

9.display files recursilbely means| including subdirecties and thier content

ls -R /ecct/apt

